Master's Journey

Founder and President – Desi Chargers Desi Chargers started as an idea to make South Asian graduate students feel represented. We practiced in dorm lounges, brought cultural choreography to life, and eventually performed at major university events — even winning iFest 2025. It’s now a thriving team of dancers and culture-shapers.

Graduate Assistant – OGISL From hosting Winter Ball and Disney trips to training new team members and handling orientation logistics, I’ve contributed to over 20 university-wide events. I was hired in my very first semester and quickly became a core part of the team.

SHRM Head of Relations & Summer Intern As Head of Relations for SHRM, I’ve curated guest panels, led collaborations, and worked on digital engagement. My summer HR internship focused on building peer-based onboarding systems, engagement reports, and campus DEI outreach.

Research & Innovation I co-led a research project on Gen Z leadership preferences using MLQ and JSS scales, then developed ThriveLocal — a start-up concept that supports relocated professionals with local connection and well-being.
